We recommended and the Local Chief Executive agreed to:

(a) establish a Gender and Focal Point System (GFPS) pursuant to PCW-DILG-DBM-NEDA Joint Memorandum Circular (JMC) No. 2013-01 to accelerate their gender mainstreaming; 

(b) stop the charging of expenses which are not directly associated with GAD; 

(c) ensure the complete implementation of activities indicated in the GPB to maximize benefits inuring to the beneficiaries; and 

(d) attribute only a portion of the agency’s major programs to the GAD budget by subjecting the program to gender analysis using the HGDG tool.

We reiterated our recommendations that the Local Chief Executive:
Instruct the head of the GSO to (i) update and maintain the required records, reports and issue the necessary Property Acknowledgement Receipt/ Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment (PAR/ARE) for those issued PPEs under the care of the end users as required under Section 123, Chapter 7, Volume 1 of the NGAS for LGUs; and (ii) to facilitate such undertaking, assign additional competent personnel to GSO in order to complete the maintenance and updating of PC records of the said office;
Issue a written order to the members of the inventory committee, indicating therein the specific period for which the subject undertaking must be completed and the period of submission of the updated physical inventory report in accordance with Section 124 of the NGAS Manual. Sanctions for the continued failure of the committee to come up with the required reports should also be expressly provided in the said order to prevent the recurrence of similar lapses in the future;
Require the reconciliation between the results of the actual physical inventory report with the accounting record pursuant to  Sections 119 and 120, Volume I, NGAS; and
Require the Accountant to review the computation of depreciation expenses and ensure that the same were based on the existing depreciable PPEs of the municipal government.

