We recommended that the Local Chief Executive direct the Office of the Market Supervisor and the Municipal Treasurer (a) to issue follow up communications and/ or demand letters to stall occupants for the settlement of their respective delinquent accounts on market rentals and goodwill obligations; 
(b) initiate legal action, if warranted, to collect the long overdue arrearages; 
(c) to make a thorough study on the appropriateness of the rental rate being charge by the municipality as compared with the current prevailing rental rate. This will enable the management to justify and support recommendation for market rental rate adjustment, subject to the approval of the Sanggunian; and 
(d) effect the necessary renewal of contract/lease agreement between the municipal government and the stall occupants.

