We recommended and the management agreed that the Local Chief Executive:
Direct the respective Heads of the Offices concerned to submit to the  Office of the Auditor a copy of Memorandum of Agreement (MOA) executed by and between the LGU and the partner NGAs in compliance with Section 6.5 of COA Circular 94-013;
Remind the Head of the Municipal Social Welfare Office (MSWO), Municipal Engineering Office (MEO) and other LGU officials concerned to prepare in advance and make available all necessary documents that would substantiate the requirements of the funding agencies in order to comply with the 60 days allowable period of submission of the same to the source agencies;
Direct the LGU officials concerned to strictly monitor the implementation of their respective projects as planned and within the prescribed time frame and take note of any gap for future inputs; and
Instruct the BuB Focal Person to coordinate with their counterpart officials from national government agencies and make follow ups in order to ascertain the reasons for non-receipt of funds from the source NGAs. This will enable the LGU to plan the next steps to be taken in case the original project is no longer viable and responsive to the needs of the intended beneficiaries.
